Name: pulmonary type ovarian small cell carcinoma
Definition: An ovarian small cell carcinoma that resembles pulmonary small cell carcinoma of neuroendocrine type.
Synonym: Multiple meningiomas of the Spinal canal and Spinal Cord

Name: hypercalcemic type ovarian small cell carcinoma
Definition: An ovarian small cell carcinoma that is associated with paraneoplastic hypercalcemia.
Synonym: Multiple meningiomas of the Spinal canal and Spinal Cord

Name: obsolete rare cancer-associated syndrome
Definition: An ovarian small cell carcinoma that is associated with paraneoplastic hypercalcemia.
Synonym: Multiple meningiomas of the Spinal canal and Spinal Cord
